Called to check on setting up this office as a primary care facility. I was told they accept Medicare Advantage plans but DO NOT take any Medicare Supplement plans, a real negative. This review will serve as a benefit to those who do not want to waste their or your time. The confusion with medical care coverage in the United States should prompt us to promote universal health care... call it socialized medicine but we need options that accommodate the well-being of people of all ages without having to spend hours.. or days.. finding health care professionals that are there to address our well-being regardless of economic or social standing. There should not be any ifs, buts and so many maybes in securing health care. This is NOT political... this is about providing humanitarian solutions to resolve health issues without incurring financial distresses. Some politicians would claim that having "options" is the American Way. But... remember the interaction between the divorced mother of three who stood up to George W. Bush, explaining that she had to work THREE JOBS to afford a livable lifestyle? And he proudly proclaimed, "Uniquely American!!!!", as if it's a positive standard of living. I ran across a doctor's office (Delicia Haynes, MD) that charges $100 as an initial fee then charges $129/month for UNLIMITED doctor visits but doesn't take ANY health insurance whatsoever! BlueCross provided me no assistance in locating a doctor who subscribes to my needs of Medicare plus their Supplement plan. It's an American shame for providing a lack of affordable, accommodating health coverage.

Harvard Family Physicians became my new clinic three years ago when I moved to Tulsa from Norman, OK.  A good family friend recommended the clinic and it has worked out very well.  My primary physician is Dr. Nesbit and I believe that he delivers professional, comprehensive  world-class care with a "close-to-home" environment.  I have seen two of the other doctors in Dr. Nesbit's absence, Drs. Van Shoyck and Wagner.  Both had access to my electronic chart and kept everyone on the same page.  I have also seen the chiropractor there, Dr. Collins and he is devoted a passionate towards his practice.  The lab staff have always done a great job and I see professionalism, courtesy and consistency with the office staff.   Several times, (on my tight budget) I have made payment arrangements and the business office has been very caring and professional concerning setting up payments when needed.  Lastly, the nurses, they have been my Florence Nightengale and helped me so many times.  Denise, Martha and Georgeanne are of the highest caliber of nurses that have ever cared for me.

The staff there is rude tried, to ask a simple question to my doctors nurse who I have worked with before, I was his patient and he is amazing, wonderful man, needs his own office. But the office mangers and the business staff are rude, no bed side manors nothing is right to them, tried to ask a question to his nurse or him and they would not let me talk to them over a 60$ something balance I owed. As far as I'm concerned they are ass holes and need to be shut down, I would love to see my primary care out of there and in his own space and office, he is an amazing amazing man and to good to be there at that clinic. If this case them to get the attention they won't that's fine. I hope someone else hears, this cause it's not right at all.

DO NOT GO HERE. This place lacks customer service, general respect, ethical conduct, and morality.  First of all, the Doctor I saw, Dr. Chasteen, made me feel very uncomfortable and unsafe. He responded to all of my health issues with prescriptions and when I told him that I felt uncomfortable with a certain prescription for legitimate reasons he did not offer an alternative. Rather, he argued to me that I should definitely take the drug. He did not treat me as a human being, but rather as another thing that he had to move through the system.  Second, what I mentioned above about prescriptions is exactly the kind of place this is. Dr. Chasteen had no concern for my health whatsoever. He was there to move me through the system as quickly as possible. For him, that meant just prescribing me things. He and the rest of Harvard Family Physicians are just there to make money.  Third, on the topic of money, Harvard Family Physicians declined to inform me that my first appointment was not the check-up appointment that I thought I was signing up for. Given my insurance, the blood test that I took and the services I received during my appointment should have been free. However, Harvard Family Physicians was negligent and did not tell me that my first appointment is actually a "get to know you" session, and therefore is not covered at all by my insurance.  Fourth, I have since been attempting to speak with customer service at Harvard Family Physicians about this misunderstanding/miscommunication/lack of communication. They have consistently been rude to me on the phone, as well as completely and utterly incompetent. They repeatedly tell me that the supervisor is in a meeting and that they'll call me back after. They do not ever call me back.  Please avoid this place at all costs. My experience here has caused me emotional, psychological, and financial strain. Do yourself a favor and go anywhere else. From my experience, you will waste your time and your money. You will also surround yourself with people that are invested an institution that does not care about you. Their actions, and particularly Dr. Chasteen's actions, are in direct violation of the Hippocratic Oath. Do not be a victim to this place.

Dr. Chasteen is excellent, personable, competent, doesn't over-diagnose or over-medicate, but he'll do what needs to be done. He always has time for whatever I need to talk about, even though he sees a lot of patients. I never feel rushed. The pharmacy in house and in house diagnostic lab are very convenient. It's a busy practice, so expect to wait sometimes to get into the lab or if you have a mid-day appointment to see the doc. Just be glad they're taking their time with the appointments before you because you know you'll get the same attention. I love the level of detail available on the patient portal both regarding care and billing-- has saved me a lot of phone calls. Recommend Dr. Chasteen highly.

Great experiences. Have our family doctor there. Their hours of operation are very convenient. Also convenient is their lab and diagnostic equipment which is I-house. We have been going here for several years.

Dr. Chasteen is wonderful - I never feel like he is just rushing me along like I have felt in the past with other doctors. He is very thorough and addresses all my questions/concerns with patience. Would highly recommend!

Disappointed... This practice was recommended to me by a family member.  I called to make an appointment that I needed scheduled ASAP and was asked a few questions and was told that they would call me back to schedule the appointment. I thought it was a little strange but just went with it... 1 day passed and no call... on the 2nd day I called to see what was going on and was told (rudely) not call back because THEY  would call ME... day 3 passed... day 4 passed... on day 5 they called me to schedule the appointment. Needless to say I had already made an appointment elsewhere- and I suggest you do the same. Good thing I didn't hold my breath. I've heard great things about the doctors and nurses however the receptionist/front desk completely ruined it for me.

Don't ever go here. Receptionist is rude. Nurses stand around doing nothing. Someone came in 20 minutes and was immediately seen, my son and I have been waiting over an hour to be seen. Horrible horrible doctors office not coming back.

The... worst... practice... ever.  If you value your family, money, and health... seek a different healthcare provider. Misdiagnosis, rude service and unsympathetic idividuals who only careabout getting as many patients in and out as fast as possible to increase thier profits.

I am a new patient of Dr Shaun and also Dr Roy. When I say that they are so incredibly nice, times that by 1000. I have never met doctors that take so much time with you as a new patient to get to know you. I am so happy there so far, I can't decribe the frustration that takes place when I meet a new doctor for the first time and I feel like they couldn't give two s**** about me. I am very happy there and if you are the type of person that wants a relationship with your doctor when you have real issues that need to be taken care of and be ttuely cared for, then you will be happy here too. :)

I love Dr. Mahaffey, and his staff especially Bonnie. My husband and I, have been going to Dr. Mahaffey for many years. In my opinion he definitely is the best Dr. anywhere. Thanks Dr. and Family Physicians for everything you do for us.

Dr. Collins the chiropractor on the 3rd floor is a nice person. He's a young chiropractor and has much still to learn, but his young woman up front is nice and considerate. However, there are a few concerns: 1) He doesn't do x-rays. Doesn't like the radiation. But I think that doing x-ray's help the doctor see what's inside and what to correct. Adjusting without them can make the chiropractor adjust wrong. 2) He gives everyone the exact same care. People aren't the same and need different type of treatment. You have to explain to him each time how the adjustment took for him to know how to help you. There are other chiropractors who don't need you to tell them what to do. I like a doctor who knows me and where it doesn't seem I have to treat myself each time. 3) He adjusts your neck in a chair. I don't like it this way, feels like someone is pulling my head off. And the motions leaves a tingling sensation down my legs. I've requested him not to adjust my neck anymore. Anyway, besides those 3 things, he's a pretty good chiropractor. And again, he's young in his business and needs more experience. I'm sure as time passes, he'll improve. As a plus: he doesn't force his adjustments!!! ^___^
Sensible, conservative, competent primary care.  Great support staff.  Good communications with all concerned.  Nobody wants to see their doctor but these guys make it a lot easier.

I have been with this clinic for 2-3 years now.  I have always had a good experience.  I have been a patient of Dr. Patrick VanSchoyck for 24 years and he is tremendous & his nurse is great.  I have also seen Dr. Muckala twice and he and his staff are wonderful.  I have had to have lab work, ultrasounds, dopplers, etc. & have had good care & pleasant experiences in every department.

Dr. Chasteen was wonderful!  He has a gentle and friendly demeanor.  He allowed plenty of time for my first visit and answered all of my questions.  His nurse was very nice, as well.  No complaints about the front office - personable and efficient.  I highly recommend this practice!!

Never have had a problem. Dr Lieberman is always courteous, and tries to cover all medical questions in the time he has. I feel he is concerned about my health. The front desk is overworked, but always seem pleasant. I think it is the way you talk to them, is the response you get back.

Dr. Van treated me when I was a kid elsewhere and now treats me at Harvard Family Physicians... he may get overwhelmed with patients because he cares and takes time with each one to make sure they're good to go before he moves on to the next one. All these bad reviews make no sense, it's a great facility, it's clean, and I've only once had to wait more than a few minutes to be seen. Overall a great doctor and I don't think I'll go elsewhere, his nurse is always there to answer any questions and I've never had a bad experience with any of the staff.
